oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of Ernest D. Warlick, Norris Fay Warlick and Ben Warlick
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Ernest Warlick and Norris Fay Warlick of Spring Creek, Madison County served in World War I and are pictured here after the war with their brother. Pvt. Ernest Warlick worked on the railroads and served in Co. A, 13th Engineers in France, in Verdun and Meuse-Argonne from September 1918 until war's end. He was a railroad brakeman before the war and lived in Jackson after the war. According to his May 8, 1919 discharge papers, he was 5'11 tall, with blue eyes, light brown hair and a ruddy complexion.
